===Etymology===
From {{etyl|it}} {{term|Italia|lang=it}} < {{etyl|la}} {{term|Italia|Ītalia|lang=la}}, via {{etyl|grc}} from {{etyl|osc}} {{term||Víteliú|lang=osc}} {{rfscript|Old Italic}} (a name for the southwestern tip of the boot of Italy), meaning "land of bulls" in Oscan; usually assumed to be a cognate of {{term|vitulus||calf|lang=la}}, despite the different length of the ''i''.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|UK|US}} {{IPA|/ˈɪ.tə.li/}}
* {{audio|En-us-Italy.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Proper noun===
{{en-proper noun}}

# A [[country]] in southern [[Europe]], one of the states of the [[European Union]]. Official name: The Italian Republic (in Italian, ''la Repubblica Italiana'').

